The Architecture Decision Record has been created as `ADR-001-notification-architecture.md`. 

I recommended **Redis Streams** over Apache Kafka because the team's size (6 people, no dedicated infra engineer) and the tight 2-week timeline make Kafka's operational overhead and learning curve a significant risk. Since Redis is already in production, it provides the necessary consumer group support and throughput to handle the 10x growth target while minimizing architectural complexity. Exactly-once semantics for billing will be handled via idempotency keys in PostgreSQL to ensure correctness.
